* Installation:
https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/

* By default, MongoDB instance stores:
 - its data files in /var/lib/mongodb
 - its log files in /var/log/mongodb

* Start MongoDB: 
sudo service mongod start

* Verify that MongoDB has started successfully (Check: [initandlisten] waiting for connections on port 27017)
tail -n 10 /var/log/mongodb/mongod.log
grep 27017 /var/log/mongodb/mongod.log



* Stop MongoDB:
sudo service mongod stop

* Restart MongoDB:
sudo service mongod restart

* Begin using MongoDB:
mongo

* Uninstall MongoDB
Stop MongoDB -> sudo apt-get purge mongodb-enterprise* 
-> sudo rm -r /var/log/mongodb
-> sudo rm -r /var/lib/mongodb






 
